<p><strong>Last updated: June 1, 2026.</strong> This Privacy Policy explains how Best Life Insurance Near Me collects, uses, discloses, and protects information when you visit this website, read our guides, or submit a form requesting life insurance information.</p>

<h2>Information we collect</h2>
<p>We may collect information you provide directly, including your name, email address, phone number, ZIP code, age range, marital status, number of children, homeowner status, annual income range, and existing coverage status when you complete the Family Protection Check or other forms.</p>
<p>When you submit a form, we may also collect consent records, including the TCPA consent text shown to you, the consent version, the time of consent, the page URL, page title, referrer, UTM campaign parameters, and browser user agent.</p>
<p>We may collect technical and usage information through server logs, analytics tools, cookies, pixels, or similar technologies, including device information, approximate location inferred from IP address, pages viewed, and interactions with forms or links.</p>

<h2>How we use information</h2>
<ul>
  <li>To respond to your request for life insurance information and to calculate your Family Protection Check results.</li>
  <li>To route life insurance inquiries to participating licensed life insurance providers, agents, and agencies.</li>
  <li>To document consent and maintain compliance records related to calls, texts, and lead submissions.</li>
  <li>To improve site content, measure marketing performance, prevent fraud, troubleshoot issues, and secure the website.</li>
  <li>To comply with applicable law, enforce our terms, and protect our rights or the rights of others.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Calls, texts, automated technology, and AI-assisted calling</h2>
<p>If you submit a form and check the consent box, you authorize Best Life Insurance Near Me and participating life insurance providers, licensed insurance agencies, financial professionals, and service partners to contact you at the phone number you provided about life insurance and family protection options. Contact may include calls, texts, prerecorded or artificial voice messages, AI-assisted calling, and automated dialing systems.</p>
<p>Your consent is not a condition of purchase. Message and data rates may apply. You may revoke consent at any time by telling a caller, replying STOP to a text where available, or contacting us through the contact page.</p>

<h2>How we share information</h2>
<p>We may share your information with vendors that host, operate, analyze, or support this website and with webhook, CRM, email, analytics, and security providers that process information on our behalf.</p>
<p>For life insurance leads, we may share submitted information and consent records with participating life insurance providers, licensed agents, agencies, or lead-management platforms so they can respond to your request.</p>
<p>We may also disclose information if required by law, subpoena, legal process, government request, or to protect rights, safety, and security.</p>

<h2>Canopy Connect</h2>
<p>If you choose to connect insurance information through Canopy Connect on our site, that data is handled per Canopy Connect's own privacy practices in addition to ours. We may receive information from the connection you authorize and use it to provide more relevant guidance. We do not store insurance account passwords. Available information depends on what you choose to connect and what your carrier provides.</p>

<h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
<p>We may use cookies, pixels, and similar technologies to remember preferences, understand traffic, attribute marketing campaigns, and improve website performance. You can adjust browser settings to block or delete cookies, but some features may not work as intended.</p>

<h2>Your choices</h2>
<ul>
  <li>You can choose not to submit a form.</li>
  <li>You can revoke phone or text consent at any time.</li>
  <li>You can request that we review, correct, or delete information associated with your submission, subject to legal and compliance retention needs.</li>
  <li>You can use browser controls or industry opt-out tools to limit certain cookies or analytics technologies.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Data retention and security</h2>
<p>We keep information for as long as reasonably necessary to respond to requests, manage partner relationships, maintain consent and compliance records, resolve disputes, enforce agreements, and satisfy legal obligations. We use reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards, but no website or transmission method is perfectly secure.</p>

<h2>Children's privacy</h2>
<p>This website is intended for adults and is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

<h2>Important disclaimer</h2>
<p>This Privacy Policy is provided for website transparency and is not legal advice. Privacy, telemarketing, insurance, and consumer protection laws can change and may vary by state. You should consult qualified counsel for legal compliance decisions.</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>Questions or privacy requests can be sent through our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.</p>
